In article <1o7pucINNeml@shelley.u.washington.edu> michaelc@u.washington.edu writes:
>Here's a challenge.  I received a MSDOS AUTOEXEC.BAT file via the MCI-Mail
>binary send file facility.  How would I go about decoding it?
>
>
>//BEGIN BINARY MAIL SEGMENT:
>begin 0777 AUTOEXEC.BAT
>*8G)E86L@;VX-"D]%
>+0$5#2$\@3T9&#0I%
...
etc. 
This is NOT a challenge, it's simply uuencoded text. First letter
indicates length-of-line, 'encoding' is done by putting 3*8-bit input
into 4*6-bit output where the output are always printable characters...
See the standard uudecode-sources.


break on
